				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Khauruk wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Howdy - I plan on dinging 49/50 soon (we'll see what fate has in store though), and am wondering how the MS2 spell stacks up vs. our other pets.  Is it worth it to just buy that spell rather than the Greater Conjuration line  from a researcher (150pp ea. on my server)?
<br />

<br />
Background:  I 2-box mage and BSTLord, have been using Air Pet for the stuns.  Mage pet almost never tanks anything, it's there for DPS.  However, how does the monster take damage (for emergencies, and suchlike)?
<br />

<br />
I did a search as I'm sure somebody else has asked a similar question, but came up w/ far too many hits to search through - if you know of a thread offhand, please feel free to just post the url.
<br />

<br />
Thanks</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Some of the MS II mobs will cast a damage shield on themselves.  If you summon one that DS itself, you can a pet with a native DS and earth pet HP with Fire pet mitigation that does not cast root.   There are a few situations where that is valuable.  However, if you are not using you pet to tank, then either use the water pet for DPS or the air pet for stuns to lessen the damage.  
<br />

<br />
The 49th fire pet is our highest DPS pet if it is getting hit and utilizing its native DS.  If it is not tanking, the water pet does more DPS because it hits for a higher average hit because it is stronger.  {The procs do the same damage, just one is fire based and the other cold based.}
<br />

<br />
If you pet is not tanking, I strongly recommend getting the water pet for DPS and air pet for reduced DPS taken because of its stun.  And in emergencies, the air pet tanks the best.<br />_________________<br />Dabrighter Blazemeister
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=449337" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=449337</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
