			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">This is one of the few things I know a little about since I spent so much time in my 50s and used my MS2 pet extensively instead of leveling up as quickly as possible (wanted to enjoy the last few levels of mage uberness, hehe).
<br />

<br />
The answer is, it depends.
<br />

<br />
The 49 pets con even to a lvl 41 character.  Focused, they con 42.  The MS2 pet cons 41 and cannot be focused.  The 51-54 pets con 45.
<br />

<br />
Back when I was in my 50s, the MS2 pet occasionally cast an innate DS on itself.  Even without its innate DS (comparable to that of the 49 fire pet), the MS2 pet has hp almost equal to 49/51 earth but with better mitigation (note that since then, I believe the earth pet in general has had its melee mitigation improved).  The advantage of the MS2 pet is that it could tank well and also melee straight up for more dps than air (53 air had a higher max, but if I recall, didn't hit for max very often).
<br />

<br />
Now, what does it depend on?
<br />

<br />
It depends on what you're fighting.  Against mobs that are at most 3-4 levels higher than the MS2 pet (that is, a mob that's maybe 45-ish), I found MS2 to be a better tank than air (maybe same melee mitigation but more hps), more dps than earth, and doesn't root.  In Dulak on boats 1 and 2, I found MS2 to be an ideal pet.  On boat 3, however, mobs were higher level and I had to switch to 57 earth (I think maybe 51 earth was a slight improvement against the higher level mobs; never even tried 49 pets in Dulak).
<br />

<br />
If fighting a mob that runs, use 49/51 earth for root if snare's not available.  If grouping, use 49/53 air for stuns.  Or, use 54 water for backstabs if you have a tank who makes the effort to spin the mob for you, or 49 water against mobs that poison if you don't have 54 water yet.  Use 49 fire for farming.  Use 52 fire for ... um ... uh ... farming newbie zones (not sure the 52 fire would survive against the griffin in East Commons!).
<br />

<br />
In your situation (2-boxing with bst), use air (stuns) or MS2 (emergency tanking).  It's hard for a mage pet to compete with the bst pet's procs anyway (this changes briefly when you're 56 and have the DDD pet whose sole purpose is to generate aggro).
<br />

<br />
I've always felt that the MS2 pet was considerably better than the 49 pets despite being a level lower than the focused 49ers, and in the right situations, even compared favorably to the 51-54 pets.  I'd say, the 49 fire pet, as the last fire pet of its kind (that is, the classic non-wizzy fire pet) is great for farming for many levels to come due to its innate DS, especially if you have the fire focus (torch) from Temple of Solusek Ro.
<br />

<br />
I don't think the MS pets self-DS anymore, so don't use this as a criterion for selecting MS2.  I think the lower level MS pets now cast a damage spell just so they cast something like other mage pets; the effect looks like claws.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
